{
  "texts": [
    "There are differences in the modelability of the language itself.",
    "The grammatical rules of English are relatively fixed, and the subject-verb-object structure is clear.",
    "The granularity of Chinese language units is fuzzy, the syntax is flexible, and the semantic dependence is long, which makes modeling relatively difficult.",
    "In addition, the difference in the number of levels also significantly affects the performance of the model.",
    "As the number of classification levels increases, the model needs to make judgments in a finer-grained label space, and the classification difficulty increases accordingly."
  ]
}